annotationA: Peroxisomal Multifunctional enzyme type 2 is a multifunctional protein harboring two separate enzyme activities: 2-enoyl-CoA hydratase 2 and 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase. They function in the peroxisomal fatty acid breakdown spiral of beta-oxidation utilizing the (R)-isomer of the CoA-containing substrate; Belongs to the short-chain dehydrogenases/reductases (SDR) family
annotationB: CG2316, isoform A; ATPase activity, coupled to transmembrane movement of substances; ATP binding; transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transmembrane transport
